The US military has sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only by the code name XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "change the game" to their advantage.
The new weapon is like a super accurate barrel
Its projectiles are laser guided with an accuracy of a few meters.
The special 25 mm caliber ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly shattering explosive, actually works like small grenades.
The munitions can be programmed in such a way that they will explode on contact with the target but also at any point on their ballistic trajectory.
It can therefore be used against an enemy who hides behind an obstacle, wall or ditch.
He is also not protected from above and when he falls on a deadly rain of steel shrapnel, it can put him out of action as well.
According to Richard Audette, who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon that uses "smart" technology.
"The soldier basically uses it in such a way that he finds the target, sends it a laser beam that determines the distance, thus obtaining a precise aiming point, according to which he corrects his site aim and pulls the trigger.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 meters."
"When you pull the trigger, the gun loads and fires at a distance of 543 meters plus or minus 1, 2, 3 meters," Audette said.
