In Bad Homburg too, Fujitsu was just a tenant.
Managing Director Bernd Wagner said: "Frankfurt-Niederrad is a prime location for us with a remarkable infrastructure."
He says the connection to the airport is of great importance to a global company like Fujitsu.
The new move of a major company within the region yesterday brought joy to the winners and disappointment to the losers.
The head of economic affairs of the municipality of Frankfurt, Markus Frank (CDU), said that once again a "global player" had been conquered.
It is an "extraordinary profession of faith relating to the location".
Fujitsu is suitable for the city and its location is an important impetus for Niederrad.
