What audience did Danish director Nicolas Winding Refn think of when shooting "Walhalla Rising"?
A Viking warrior (Mads Mikkelsen) possessing only one eye is taken prisoner; He frees himself from his executioner and, with almost supernatural force, eliminates his opponents one after the other. This seems ideal for young male viewers looking for bloody action, precisely because our hero uses brutal assassination methods. When he is in a bad mood, he tears out the intestines of his enemies without waiting for them to be dead.
