"These people received very little follow-up after the surrender," said Sok Leang of the Center for Justice and Reconciliation, which organizes public forums across Cambodia, including Anlong Veng.
"They are imbued with the regime's utopian agrarian ideology."
"They were raised in an environment where doing business is a foreign concept."
