$200 million more for "the supplier"
The City Council of Mazatlán pays another cheque to the questioned owner of the electrical equipment company.
Another cheque of about 200 thousand pesos in favor of Lorena Guadalupe Camacho Palazuelos was issued by the City Council.
With it, the amount paid this second half to the owner of the electrical equipment company amounts to 1,200,000 pesos.
According to the transparency page of the Municipality, this last cheque number 9258447 was issued on November 16 for the amount of 200 thousand 144.56 pesos, in concept of "liquidation of accounts payable".
Treasurer Luis Miguel López Moreno had said that the Municipality would pay other amounts to this supplier, who was observed by the Superior Audit of the State to sell at a higher price.
What has not been reported is the total debt and, therefore, how many checks will still be issued in favor of Camacho Palazuelos.
"We didn't buy anything, we just pay him what we owe him, like the rest of the suppliers," he said in an interview.
The last cheques "reappeared" in the last quarter of the year: on September 24, two on October 15, October 19, October 29 and the latter, November 16.
Even if the supplier has not yet published in the Official Gazette of the State, according to the provisions of the Law when a company is questioned by ASE, to prevent other governments from using its services, the Treasurer assured that they have not used its services again.
All this, after July 25, Noroeste had published a revision of the checks that the City Council issues to its suppliers, revealing that in the interval March 2008 - July 2010, in the triennium of Mayor Jorge Abel López Sánchez, the Municipality paid Camacho Palazuelos more than 10 million pesos, through 42 checks.
He also transacted with Jumapam, cashing checks for more than 3 million pesos.
